cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SY

The paper discusses the use of Machine Learning and Deep Learning techniques to predict plant growth and yield in greenhouse environments. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves image analysis and computer vision techniques to monitor plant growth, which suggests the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the second most likely. The use of neural networks and other AI techniques further supports the inclusion of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of recurrent neural networks, which suggests the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of control systems to regulate the greenhouse environment, which suggests the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a possible sub-category.
